  <description><![CDATA[<p>Ideally located in Sauze's historic centre, the Hotel Assietta is just three minutes walk from Clotes lift and <span>close to all the shops, restaurants and bars</span> you could need. This popular family-run hotel offers good accommodation and a friendly informal atmosphere in relaxed surroundings.</p>
<h2>Central location</h2>
<p>Just three minutes walk from the Clotes lift, giving you access to the whole <a data-udi="umb://document/342fdefebf5f411d9f973a480753767c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/342fdefebf5f411d9f973a480753767c}" title="Milky Way Ski Area">Milky Way Ski Area. </a></p>
<p>The ski bus for the Sportinia lift stops just outside.</p>
<h2>Lively sun terrace</h2>
<p>A highlight of the Hotel Assietta is the sunny outdoor terrace, ideal for a few après-ski drinks with friends after a day on the slopes. </p>
<p>You can experience some of <a data-udi="umb://document/a0b1d3c577424320a9af2e1af08b6887" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a0b1d3c577424320a9af2e1af08b6887}" title="Sauze d'Oulx">Sauze d'Oulx's</a> famous après scene at the Assietta bar, with live DJ sets once a week from 3:30pm to 6:30pm.</p>
<p>The hotel can also arrange a wine tasting on request to try out some of the region's excellent <a data-udi="umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902" href="/{localLink:umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902}" title="Italy">Italian</a> wines <span>(payable locally).</span></p>
<h2>Italian food</h2>
<p><span>Dinner is taken in the hotel's à la carte restaurant or stube and has a varied menu with traditional Italian dishes. Try out the wide selection of drinks including some the finest Piemonte wines (payable locally).</span></p>
<p>Dining never gets dull on half board with three speciality nights per week, mountain meal night, pizza night, and typical gala dinner.</p>]]></description>
